			\textbf{3.4 Comments and Special Characters} \bigskip			

			Comments in programming are explanations or annotations in the source code that intend to make the code easier for human readers to
			understand and that are usually ignored by the compiler or interpreter (and hence not executed). 
			In \LaTeX{} comments are marked through the percentage sign (\textit{\%}). 

		\end{flushleft} 

